description:
The Changi Murals are a series of five paintings on the major themes of the Bible painted by Stanley Warren, a British Bombardier and prisoner-of-war interned at the Changi Prison, during the Japanese occupation of Singapore in World War 2. His murals were completed under difficult conditions of sickness, limited materials and hardships. This is the story of how their message of universal love and forgiveness uplifed the spirits and brought hope to the prisoners of war when they sought refuge in the prison chapel.

Gary Kent is the speaker for *The Incredible Journey* media ministry. He holds a B.A. in Theology, M.A. in Ancient History & Archaeology, and M. in Divinity.
